	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The Sega Mega Drive is only called &quot;Genesis&quot; in the United States, (and <em>possibly</em> in Canada - this would have to be verified). In all other countries of the world, it is called &quot;Sega Mega Drive&quot;, and &quot;Genesis&quot; refers to the first book of the Torah/Old Testament and to a music pop group from the 80s.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


