		<td><b>Re: Sega Genesis again in production in Brazil as of 2016</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Conjecture:<br />It's possible for the input layer to be emulated even if the CPU, memory controller, VDP, and FM aren't. The front-end processor reads the gamepads 60 times a second and then hands the signal off to the Mega Drive SoC hardware. This means things relying on nonstandard read timing, such as the mouse, won't work for much the same reason that anything but a standard NES controller won't work through a Four Score or Satellite adapter.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


